#Logistic Regression ##Confed and Year

model_year <- glm(confed ~ year, data = gss, family = binomial)
summary(model_year)
## 
## Call:
## glm(formula = confed ~ year, family = binomial, data = gss)
## 
## Coefficients:
##              Estimate Std. Error z value Pr(>|z|)

## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
## 
## (Dispersion parameter for binomial family taken to be 1)
## 
##     Null deviance: 6102.7  on 4612  degrees of freedom
## Residual deviance: 5830.0  on 4611  degrees of freedom
## AIC: 5834
## 
## Number of Fisher Scoring iterations: 4
1 - (model_year$deviance / model_year$null.deviance)
## [1] 0.04469016
gss$predicted_prob_year <- predict(model_year, type = "response")
gss$predicted_class_year <- ifelse(gss$predicted_prob_year > 0.5, 1, 0)

roc_year <- roc(polviews ~ predicted_prob_year, data = gss)
## Setting levels: control = 0, case = 1
## Setting direction: controls < cases
roc_year$auc
## Area under the curve: 0.4586
plot(roc_year)
